OL,3,CHandling error by ambulance technician
OL,4,Ccontributed to Grandmother's death
OL,6,FWhile the coroner did not find that
OL,7,Fthis played a role in Doreen's death,
OL,8,Fhe did have sufficient concerns about
OL,9,Fthe accuracy of the nursing charts at
OL,10,Fthe Royal Blackburn to direct the
OL,11,Fhospital to provide full details
OL,12,Fwithin 28 days of how the charts are
OL,13,Faudited and checked to ensure adequate
OL,14,Fmonitoring.
OL,16,FIf the coroner is not satisfied with
OL,17,FBlackburn's response, or if they miss
OL,18,Fthis deadline, he has the power to
OL,19,Fmake a Prevention of Future Deaths
OL,20,FRegulation 28 report against the
OL,21,Fhospital.
